Upchar generates anonymized, aggregated medicine search intelligence based on user interactions with its AI medicine finder and symptom analyzer. 
This data—when processed ethically and without personal identifiers—becomes a powerful resource for healthcare stakeholders who need real-world,
real-time signals about medication demand.
A sortable table / bar graph showing:

Medicine name

% share of searches

Region of highest demand

Category (antibiotic, painkiller, antacid, allergy meds, etc.)

A map of India (or state) with heat colors showing:

High demand regions

Sudden spikes

Low supply risk

Seasonal shift zones

Example:
Mumbai: ↑ Flu meds
Delhi: ↑ Antacids
Chennai: ↑ Allergy meds

Line charts showing how medicine demand changes month-wise.

Flu medicines → peaks in winter

ORS → peaks in summer

Antihistamines → monsoon spikes

This helps companies prepare inventory in advance.

Pie/Bar charts for:

Painkillers

Antibiotics

Allergy meds

Gastric meds

Diabetes meds

Cold & cough segment

Stakeholders can filter by:

city

state

age group

Shows what substitutes users search for after scanning an image or entering a medicine.

Dashboard flags high-risk signals:

spike in antibiotic searches

rise in steroid medicines

increase in sleep-inducing drugs

misuse patterns

Government bodies love this.
